2 HOUSE BILL 273
1 Article – Insurance
2 15–1208.1.
3 (c) All small employer health benefit plans shall provide a special enrollment
4 period during which the following individuals may be enrolled under the health benefit
5 plan:
6 (1) an individual who becomes a dependent of the eligible employee
7 through marriage, birth, adoption, placement for adoption, or placement for foster care;
8 (2) an eligible employee who acquires a new dependent through marriage,
9 birth, adoption, placement for adoption, placement for foster care, or through a child
10 support order or other court order;
11 (3) the spouse of an eligible employee at the birth or adoption of a child,
12 placement of a child for foster care, or through a child support order or other court order,
13 provided the spouse is otherwise eligible for coverage;
14 (4) at the option of the SHOP Exchange, an enrollee who is the eligible
15 employee or the spouse of the eligible employee, if:
16 (i) the enrollee loses a dependent or is no longer considered to be a
17 dependent due to divorce or legal separation; or
18 (ii) the employee or the employee’s dependent dies; and
19 (5) (i) an eligible employee who becomes pregnant, as confirmed by a
20 health care practitioner; and
21 (ii) an eligible employee’s spouse or dependent who becomes
22 pregnant, as confirmed by a health care practitioner, provided the spouse or dependent is
23 otherwise eligible for coverage.
24 (f) (1) If an eligible employee enrolls any of the individuals described in
25 subsection (c)(1) through (4) of this section during the first 31 days of the special enrollment
26 period, the coverage shall become effective as follows:
27 (v) in the case of a dependent added due to a child support order or
28 any other court order:
29 1. the date the child support order or other court order is
30 effective; or
31 2. for SHOP Exchange plans, if ALLOWED BY the SHOP
32 Exchange [permits] AND SELECTED BY the eligible employee [to select an effective date
33 based on the date the plan selection is received by the SHOP Exchange:

HOUSE BILL 273 3
1 A.], the first day of the month following receipt of the plan
2 selection[, if the plan selection is received between the first and fifteenth day, inclusive, of
3 the month; and
4 B. the first day of the second month following receipt of the
5 plan selection, if the plan selection is received between the sixteenth and the last day,
6 inclusive, of the month].
7 (g) If the SHOP Exchange [permits] ALLOWS the special enrollment periods
8 described in subsection (c)(4) of this section, the coverage shall become effective as follows:
9 (1) for special enrollment periods in the SHOP Exchange due to death of
10 the employee or dependent[:
11 (i)], the first day of the month following plan selection; [or
12 (ii) if the SHOP Exchange permits the eligible employee to select an
13 effective date based on the date the plan selection is received by the SHOP Exchange:
14 1. the first day of the month following receipt of the plan
15 selection, if the plan selection is received between the first and fifteenth day, inclusive, of
16 the month; and
17 2. the first day of the second month following receipt of the
18 plan selection, if the plan selection is received between the sixteenth and the last day,
19 inclusive, of the month;] and
20 (2) for special enrollment periods in the SHOP Exchange due to divorce or
21 legal separation, [if the plan selection is received by the SHOP Exchange:
22 (i) between the first and fifteenth day, inclusive, of the month,] the
23 first day of the month following receipt of the plan selection[; and
24 (ii) between the sixteenth and the last day, inclusive, of the month,
25 the first day of the second month following receipt of the plan selection].
26 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
27 October 1, 2026.

